</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kruggan>Kruggan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/14/03 11:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5395.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: X-server question (not x-server trade offer)</span><hr size=1> I'll be helpful.  I restarted on FV from my old server but was determined not to be dirt poor again.  Call me nuts, but after 4 years, 3 servers, and 6 characters over lvl 60 that I levelled myself individually, somehow I feel I've earned to the right not to start with 0pp in the bank.  When I made the server switch, I advertised in the auction channel on both servers for a short time offering to trade PP between servers (50k on FV for 75k on my old server).  After a few days I found a bite, and after some cautious trading (small increments) - I started on FV with some cash.  <br>
<br>
Now, there are some who look down on this practice in a self-righteous, narrow-minded manner.  I don't go seeking those out to bash them - everyone has a right to their opinion.  However, I don't mind saying this to those who love using the phrase &quot;Go and earn the way the rest of us did&quot;.  I did earn it.  I've probably spent more time earning it than the majority have.  If folks don't like it, they can kiss my white, hairy ogre behind.  There is a difference, however, between someone who has invested quite a bit of time in the game over the years, starting out with some coin and those who simply buy PP for real money and twink out a toon (and have no experience in the game).  <br>
<br>
Your best bet is probably going to be to do whatever you do discreetly and cautiously.  And, it's probably wise not to advertise too openly unless you're willing to wear a flame jacket as you've seen here from some.<br>
<br>
