<br>
Firiona Vie is the role playing server. Many folks see us only as a blue server with a different rule set. This is what most &quot;self ritous&quot; residents are trying to defend against.  Cross server trading, and the &quot;gamer&quot; mentality are symptoms of the blue servers that many came to FV to get away from.<br>
<br>
Although, now there really is no point in trying to defend what's left of the RP server.  There are still roleplayers around, but that golden dream of a place where just about everyone is there for character interaction first, and loot second, is all but dead.<br>
<br>
New players are always welcome. But every time a thread like this is born, a piece of the role playing server decays.  I think it's becoming more accepted lately simply because Firiona Vie has lost much of it's unique atmosphere.  A year ago a thread like this would have had you tarred and feathered.  However, so many bluebies have diluted the community, that nobody really seems to care anymore.<br>
<br>
Oh, and BTW, I could give a rats ass about your 3 level 60 characters on your old server.<br>
